<p>[^1] Yes, I use both. For now. I also keep a digital calendar plus a monthly spread in my paper planner, and a wall calendar for the rest of the family to refer to. It might sound like a lot to keep in sync, but for me the writing and re-writing of appointments and tasks is an important part of having them seem real and achievable. Itâ€™s a way of anchoring me to them, because I am remarkably prone to drift from my moorings and wander aimlessly all day long. I acknowledge that this kind of overlap will be unnecessarily complex for some. Itâ€™s perfectly fine to use just one, if that does the job for your needs.</p>
